 strength at high energies E ≥ V. At these energies new particles with the mass characterized by the scale V can be copiously produced, as well as their exchange is not suppressed. At smaller energies E < V these particles can be produced in virtual states and their effects are suppressed by some power of (E/V). For high energy scale V , cosmology, predicting the stages of early Universe with very high energy density, becomes natural laboratory of new physics. Its observable signatures require some messengers, which retain information on the processes in the very early Universe and provide their confrontation with the astrophysical data on the phenomena, taking place at much},
